</p><p class="- topic/p "> In any case the following files should be attached to the PR: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> TraceData
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">As a reference: see 
<xref keyref="LogfilesandColorado" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-818EBAA7-B43E-4056-9C21-C1634AC4D72B.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text Log files and Colorado system?>Log files and Colorado system</xref> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The files should be created as close as possible created after the problem occurred. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The TraceData will be created automatically after an MRE and can be found in the log store (see picture). 
</p><fig id="GUID-D167DECF-72E7-441F-9FFF-8954EE672A3F" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-B23D90B5-ED5C-48E3-8E1B-FD28A4FC4555-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-B23D90B5-ED5C-48E3-8E1B-FD28A4FC4555-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-53EB6263-AAA9-465D-BCB2-647DFAC17B6C" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">What if the system starts with an error ?</title><p class="- topic/p ">If this happens you can start the system in zero SDS. In Zero SDS logging retrieval is always possible. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See<xref keyref="ZeroSDS" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-7B8634B6-A3A4-4DAA-BF9D-10586F2D4E53.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text How to enter Zero SDS?>How to enter Zero SDS</xref> 
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-AE482382-4925-4EFB-985E-8DF8BE795C1D.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Preventive maintenance</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
